ibution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Mrs. William Bucton was born in 1230, in Sedgebrook, Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom. She married William Bucton in 1250, in Sedgebrook, Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter."},"et":{"1230–Deceased":"1230–Surnud","1225–Male":"1225–Surnud","1253–Female":"1253–Surnud","1230–Female":"1230–Surnud","1225":"1225","1253":"1253","1230":"1230","Sedgebrook, , Lincolnshire, England":"Sedgebrook, Lincolnshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1230–Deceased":"1230–Kuollut","1225–Male":"1225–Kuollut","1253–Female":"1253–Kuollut","1230–Female":"1230–Kuollut","1225":"1225","1253":"1253","1230":"1230","Sedgebrook, , Lincolnshire, England":"Sedgebrook, Lincolnshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1230–Deceased":"1230–Décédée","1225–Male":"1225–Décédé","1253–Female":"1253–Décédée","1230–Female":"1230–Décédée","1225":"1225","1253":"1253","1230":"1230","Sedgebrook, , Lincolnshire, England":"Sedgebrook, Lincolnshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Mrs. William Bucton est née en 1230, à Sedgebrook, Lincolnshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Elle a épousé William Bucton en 1250, à Sedgebrook, Lincolnshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fille."},"de":{"1230–Deceased":